@startuml state_ownership
' Revised 2026-05-13: applied audit_23/Wave-1-fix amendments
!include dark-theme.puml
title State / source-of-truth audit - every fact and where it lives

' Forward-declare so notes can reference it from inside the package below.
' (PlantUML chokes on `note bottom of X` when X is declared later.)
component NightLightProvider as NLP

' ----- "Current brightness" - 4 places per monitor -----
package "Current brightness per monitor" $TINT_RED {
  [DDC monitor (HW)\n*authoritative source*]                        as DDCHW
  [MonitorInfo.Brightness\n(0-100)\nUI mirror / user intent]        as MIB
  [MonitorInfo.CurveTargetBrightness\n(curve-driven indicator;\nactive iff IsCurveDriven;\nmaster gated on IsCurveDriven - H-29)] as MICT
  [MonitorInfo.VirtualBrightness\nmaster slider unclamped]          as MIV
  [MonitorInfo.IsReadDegraded\n(orthogonal to SliderState;\nslider stays operable while\nreads fail - cf2e77e)] as MIRD
  [MonitorInfo.IsDragging\n(curve-apply skip flag - H-10;\nset by BFL on slider thumb drag)] as MIDR
  component "MonitorEntry.NormCurveXs/Ys +\nFloorPercent / CeilingPercent\n(per-monitor norm curve\nconsumed by DoBrightnessWriteAsync)" as MENC
  component "KnownDisplayEntry.LastBusBrightness\n(percent; stamped in MonitorService\nat write-success site;\nseed on cold-start +\nrecovery promote)" as KDLB
  component "BrightnessProfile.MonitorStates[]\n(persisted in profiles.xml)" as BPM
  DDCHW <-> MIB  : EnqueueDirectBrightness\n(throttled write -> retry -> verify)
  MICT  ..> DDCHW : drained by EnvironmentalCurveService\nthrough MonitorService throttler\n(skip when IsDragging - H-10)
  MIB   ..> MIV   : master / individual sync
  MIB   ..> BPM   : on profile Save
  MENC  ..> DDCHW : per-monitor floor/ceiling\nand norm curve gating
  KDLB  ..> MIB  : cold-start seed for new-monitor\nbranch + recovery promote
}

note as N_THROTTLE $TINT_RED
  Latest-pending-wins lives in
  MonitorService._writeThrottler (AsyncThrottler<string>,
  per-DeviceID key). MonitorEntry only carries
  LastEnqueuedPercentage (dedupe across completed
  writes) - the queue itself is on the throttler.
end note
N_THROTTLE .. MICT

' ----- "Night-light" - now backend-cached, not 4-place -----
package "Night-light state" $TINT_BLUE {
  [Windows BlueLightReduction\n(CloudStore / SettingsHandler\n*OS SoT*)]                  as NLOS
  [AppSettings.NightLightFallbackMode\n(backend selector: Auto /\nRegistry / GammaRamp /\nSettingsHandler)]  as ASNLM
  [AppSettings.NightLightLastNonZeroStrength\n(restore-on-toggle memo, 0-100)]            as ASNLR
  [AppSettings.TurnOffNightLightAtZeroStrength\nAppSettings.NightLightPDBDownloadTimeoutSeconds] as ASNLT
  [BrightnessFlyout._isNightLightActive\n+ NightLightMonitor.Brightness\n(UI mirror, polled from NLP)] as BFNL
  [NightLightMonitor.CurveTargetBrightness\n(curve indicator)]                            as NLCT
  [BrightnessProfile.NightLight\n(0-100, persisted)]                                      as BPN
  ASNLM ..> NLP : settings-Changed -> InvalidateBackendCache
  ASNLR <.. NLP : SetStrength persists\nlast non-zero
  BFNL  ..> NLP : SetStrength on slider release\n+ slider zero-trap toggle
  NLCT  ..> NLP : SetStrength per curve tick\n(persistAsLastUserValue=false)
  BPN   ..> NLP : on profile activate
  NLP   <-> NLOS
}

note bottom of NLP
  NightLightProvider is a static facade with
  _backendCached / _lastResolvedBackend /
  _lastResolvedFallbackMode under _gate.
  Resolves once to Registry or SettingsHandler;
  Auto/GammaRamp currently fall through to Registry.
  AppSettings.Changed re-probes only when the
  fallback-mode field actually moved.
end note

' ----- Active profile / curve -----
package "Active profile / curve" $TINT_GREEN {
  [ProfileManager._selectedIndex]                      as PMI
  component "ProfileManager.Profiles\n(ProfileCollection,\npersisted to profiles.xml)" as PPI
  [ProfileManager.HasUnsavedChanges]                   as HUC
  [BrightnessFlyout.IsBrightnessCurveEnabled\nBrightnessFlyout.IsNightLightCurveEnabled\n(mirrored to EnvironmentalCurveService\n+ persisted on AppSettings)] as FCEN
  [EnvironmentalCurveService\n._cachedShiftedCurve\n(sun-shifted clone;\nkey = (sourceCurveRef,\nVersion, Date, Lat, Lon, DST) - H-28)] as ECS_CACHE
  [EnvironmentalCurveService\n._isInDisabledPeriod\n+ _isSuspended (preview sweep)] as ECS_FLAGS
  [IsBrightnessCurveEnabledQuery + IsInDisabledPeriodQuery\n(live closures passed to MonitorService\nso physical brightness recovery consults real-time\nengagement / disabled-period - H-03)] as CFCQ
  PMI -> PPI
  PPI ..> ECS_CACHE : cached lazily;\nkeyed by source-curve identity\nplus date / location / DST / Version
  FCEN ..> ECS_CACHE : engages timer\n+ tick apply
  FCEN ..> CFCQ : live read by recovery /\nharmonize call sites
  ECS_FLAGS ..> CFCQ
}

' ----- Slider visible state (single enum) -----
package "Slider visible / behavioural state" $TINT_BLUE {
  [MonitorInfo.SliderState\n(enum: Enabled / Disabled /\nFailed / CurveActive /\nCurveSleeping / CurveReleased)] as SS
  [SliderStateMachine\n(pure transition fns)]                      as SSM
  [MonitorInfo._preFailureSliderState\n-> WasCurveDrivenBeforeFailure] as SSPRE
  component "BrightnessProfile.MonitorStates[i]\n.IsSliderEnabled\n(persisted: 'user excluded?')" as BPMS
  SSM ..> SS  : caller writes result back\n(setter raises one PropertyChanged)
  SS  ..> SSPRE : stash on transition into Failed
  SS  ..> BPMS : on profile Save\n(SliderState != Disabled)
}

' ----- Monitor connection list -----
package "Monitor connection list" $TINT_AMBER {
  [MonitorService.Monitors\n(ObservableCollection,\nflyout binds direct)]              as MSM
  component "KnownDisplaysStore\n(displays.json,\nEDID-keyed history)"                 as KDS
  [KnownDisplayEntry\n.WasEverDDCCapable\n(sticky)]                                    as ASKD
  component "AppSettings.KnownDisplays[]\n(legacy, migrated to KDS\non first load)"     as ASK
  component "AppSettings.MonitorOrder[]\nAppSettings.MonitorOverrides[]"               as ASO
  MSM ..> KDS : on Refresh()\n(DDC-capability promotion)
  KDS ..> ASKD
  ASK ..> KDS : one-shot first-run migration
  MSM ..> ASO : reads ordering / per-monitor overrides
}

' ----- Sun position -----
package "Sun / time-of-day" $TINT_PURPLE {
  [DateTime.Now\nsampled fresh per tick]                              as DTN
  [SPACalculator output\n(via SunShifter, src/Utils)]                 as SPA
  [EnvironmentalCurve.BrightnessAnchor\nEnvironmentalCurve.DisabledPeriodAnchor\n(2x SunAnchor record:\nDate, Lat, Lon, UseDaylightSavings)] as ECA
  [AppSettings.EnvironmentalLatitude\n/EnvironmentalLongitude\n(global geo SoT)]       as ASGEO
  DTN -> SPA
  ASGEO -> SPA
  SPA -> ECA : invalidates clone\nif date / lat / lon / DST differ
}

' ----- Hotkeys -----
package "Hotkey registrations" $TINT_TEAL {
  component "AppSettings.Hotkeys\n(List<HotkeyBinding>,\npersisted SoT)"               as ASH
  [GlobalHotkeyService._byId\n(live RegisterHotKey IDs;\nrebuilt on Apply)]            as GHS
  ASH ..> GHS : Apply diff-and-replace\n(on settings save\n+ MonitorsRefreshed)
}

' ----- Tray icon -----
package "Tray icon state" $TINT_AMBER {
  [TrayIconManager._iconStyle\n+ _isOnCooldown / _updatePending]                       as TIM
  [AppSettings.TrayIconStyle\nAppSettings.DynamicIconBrightnessTracking\nAppSettings.TrayIcon{,Bright,Dim}Color] as ASTI
  ASTI ..> TIM : settings-Changed -> reapply
}

' ----- Theme -----
package "Theme" $TINT_PINK {
  component "AppTheme\n(theme.xml; ThemeColor pairs,\nglyphs, profile-button defaults)" as APT
  [AppTheme.IsLightTheme\n(runtime; SystemEvents.UserPreferenceChanged\nfiltered to UserPreferenceCategory.General;\nregkey read on-demand inside handler)] as APTL
  [AppSettings.ThemeMode\n(System / Light / Dark)]            as ASTM
  [AppSettings NullableThemeColor overrides\n(Text, Background, TrayIcon*, Environmental*Curve, etc.)] as ASCOL
  APTL ..> APT
  ASTM ..> APT : ResolveEffectiveIsLightTheme
  ASCOL ..> APT : per-color override wins\nover ThemeColor default
}

note as N_REFRESH $TINT_GREEN
  **Refresh reentrancy guard (Wave 2 fix - H-01):**
  MonitorService.Refresh captures snapshots
  (latestByID, edidKeyByID, nameOverridesByEDID,
  strategyChanged) in Phase A and consumes them
  in deferred Phase B at +1500 ms. A new
  _refreshGen Volatile counter bumps on every
  Refresh entry; the deferred Phase B closure
  compares its captured gen against the current
  value and bails when superseded. Sweep at
  +2 s / +5 s no longer races the initial
  Phase B.
end note

note as N_SEED $TINT_AMBER
  **MasterMonitor.Brightness seed:**
  BrightnessFlyout ctor seeds from
  AppSettings.LastMasterBrightness ?? 100.
  After acquisition, the master is recomputed from
  connected hardware-functional display values using
  AppSettings.MasterSliderMode (lowest / average / highest).
  This recompute is UI-only and does not replay DDC writes.
end note

note as N1
  **Multiple sources of truth still flagged:**
  - Brightness mirrored across 4 places
    (HW, MonitorInfo.Brightness,
    CurveTargetBrightness, profile state).
    Curve target intentionally separated from
    user-driven Brightness.
  - Night-light SoT is the OS (CloudStore or
    SettingsHandler); we cache the resolved
    backend in NightLightProvider, mirror live
    state on _isNightLightActive and on the
    NightLightMonitor pseudo-row.
  - Curve-engagement flag has 3 mirrors:
    BrightnessFlyout.IsBrightnessCurveEnabled,
    EnvironmentalCurveService.Is*CurveEnabled,
    AppSettings.Environmental*CurveEnabled
    (persistence). Flyout setter writes all three.
  - KnownDisplays now lives in displays.json
    (KnownDisplaysStore). AppSettings.KnownDisplays
    survives only as the one-shot migration source.
  - SunAnchor record collapses what used to be 8
    flat anchor fields into 2 structs (curve +
    disabled-period); XML shape preserved by flat
    Last*SunShift{Date,Lat,Lon,UseDaylightSavings}
    properties that route through the struct.
  - Persisted IsSliderEnabled bool is a lossy
    projection of SliderState (only Disabled vs
    not-Disabled survives Save / Apply). Curve /
    sleep / failed states reconstitute on load
    from curve flags + DDC capability instead.
end note

@enduml
